    Kinbit link`
    ( ./kinbit_link
    + typology
        ( genetic bitlink
            * kinbit link
    + formation
        ( additional to surtype formation
        * import references
    + function
        ( additional to surtype function
        - forms a kinbit tree
        - casts a vote of approval for the mother kinbit and its progenitors
            < Votorola style, transitive vote flow ('delegate cascade') in a recombinant text
                ( http://reluk.ca/project/votorola/d/theory.xht#action-norm
            - effective iff
                & the waycast is public
                    ( else at most it forms a vote without casting it
                & the daughter kinbit is an imported waybit
                & the daughter kinbit is either on way or begets on-way progeny
            - casts a vote whereby the caster (vote caster ≡ waycaster) formally approves (votes for)
              the content of the mother kinbit and (by transitive vote flow) each of its progenitors
              that lies outside the waycast
            - general effect
                - to publicly use another's waybit is to vote for it
                    - use implies approval
                    ( cf. "voting with one's feet"

